We need to prove that for any two measurable sets $w_1$ and $w_2$, the following equation holds:
$P(w_1 \cap w_2) = P(w_1) \cdot P(w_2)$,
where $P(s)$ is the projection operator defined as $P(s) = \text{continuousLinearMapOfBilin}(\text{toBoundedBilin}(s, \ldots))$.

